reviews.review_text:
Fun & Hot Day At The Zoo - Jerry's 40th B-Day I wake up at Mason’s apartment in Austin the next morning the definition of hung over. Thankfully Randy jumps behind the wheel and the other guy is riding shotgun and I am in the back passed out as we head to Oklahoma City.

We arrive at the Zoo (literally), park and head for the stage. Show is soon and it is hot! I ask Randy to please bring me some water. Alas he returns with a jug of draft beer. I’m dosed and ready to go.

The show was not a fireworks show as much as a really good day at the park.
Jack Straw opened as we all settled in for the late afternoon ride. Jerry eased the temperature with a sweet They Love Each Other and Bob followed with a fine C.C Rider. Tennessee Jed loped along. Cowboy hour was up  next as Bob did Me & My Uncle & Big River. And something I love a China > Rider 1st set closer.  

Is there anything better than Playing In The Band to open a set? Nope! After a nice jam lo & behold my 1st Aiko-Aiko appeared. It was a joy as all the faces around me lit up and dancers got down! Aiko was GRATE! Lost Sailor smooth sailed ahead and then boogie time again with Saint of Circumstance. Drums > Space was a blur due to the heat. But then The Wheel came rolling out and the place came alive again. The band wound back to Playing Reprise and Jerry eased into Black Peter. It was mournfully delightful. Time to boogie down the rest of the way with Around & Around and US Blues. 

And another show had come & gone. 

We were at the Waffle House at midnight. Only 2 other couples in the place sharing a table nearby. Suddenly the power went off and everyone is sitting in the dark. Suddenly a woman’s voice cries out, “Daniel get you hand off my leg!!!”. Just then the lights come on and everyone in the place laughs their asses off. 
The day ended with smiles all around.
